arts.ttl: Ivanovic scores unique header as Millwall beat Dagenham
arts.sum: Mihailo Ivanovic scores an unusual goal as Millwall comfortably beat National League Dagenham and Redbridge to progress to the fourth round of the FA Cup.

arts.ttl: Alex Neil delivers verdict as Millwall set up Leeds FA Cup clash following Dagenham & Redbridge win
arts.sum: Millwall put the game to bed with two goals in the final 20 minutes after Dagenham stepped things up after the break to hand Neil his first win in charge and set up a fourth round tie away at Leeds United. I thought when we got the second goal that’s probably when the game started to get away from them a little bit.

arts.ttl: Mihailo Ivanovic’s bizarre goal inspires Millwall to FA Cup win over Dagenham
arts.sum: This has certainly been a week to remember for three members of the Young family. Yet after Everton’s Ashley was cruelly denied the chance to face his son Tyler against Peterborough, Dagenham & Redbridge’s interim manager Lewis couldn’t quite conjure up an FA Cup shock as a bizarre improvised finish from Mihailo Ivanovic helped Millwall knock out the last non-league team still left standing in this year’s competition. A trip to face Leeds in the fourth round awaits for Alex Neil and his side after second-half goals from Casper De Norre and the substitute Ra’ess Bangura-Williams on his debut ensured the former Norwich and Sunderland manager picked up a first win since taking over from Neil Harris. But the night still belonged to Dagenham and their supporters, who almost outnumbered a disappointingly low turnout from the home fans and made their presence felt throughout. Continue reading...

arts.ttl: Ra’ess Bangura-Williams adds gloss with debut goal as Millwall see off Dagenham
arts.sum: Dagenham gifted Mihailo Ivanovic a first-half opener before Casper De Norre and Bangura-Williams struck.

arts.ttl: Millwall defender Joe Bryan: We’ll show maximum respect to Dagenham & Redbridge
arts.sum: Joe Bryan has made it clear that none of Millwall’s players will be visualising a plum FA Cup fourth round draw before they face Dagenham and Redbridge at The Den on Monday night. “We need to beat Dagenham and not think too far past Monday’s game.
